1
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:02,200
Guards!

2
00:01:02,359 --> 00:01:03,799
Prince Chengle and his accomplice are here!

3
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:04,599
Come and arrest me!

4
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:05,040
Are you crazy?

5
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:05,480
Get out of here, now!

6
00:01:05,719 --> 00:01:06,159
Seize them!

7
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:07,200
If you're the criminal, I'm your accomplice.

8
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,640
We deserve what's coming.

9
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:12,000
Qi Zhi, as the informant,

10
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,079
his merits offset his crimes.

11
00:01:13,079 --> 00:01:14,040
He's released without charge.

12
00:01:34,079 --> 00:01:36,079
Prince Chengle has been sentenced to death.

13
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:38,439
We've all heard about it.

14
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,200
Who would've thought

15
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,200
my Royal Brother was really that kind of person.

16
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,920
Prince Chengle was kind of his idol.

17
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:55,959
Looks like it completely broke his heart.

18
00:01:57,319 --> 00:01:58,760
You go and comfort him.

19
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:01,040
You'd better go instead.

20
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,799
I wouldn't know what to say.

21
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:16,800
Don't stand so close to me.

22
00:02:16,879 --> 00:02:18,280
I can only tell the truth right now.

23
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,680
I'll end up offending you again.

24
00:02:21,639 --> 00:02:22,439
It's fine.

25
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,560
This princess is in a good mood today.

26
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,159
I won't hit anyone.

27
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:30,879
I've always believed

28
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:32,159
that education leads people to virtue.

29
00:02:33,599 --> 00:02:36,560
Only an uneducated brute lacks morals.

30
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:38,520
But I never expected

31
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:39,960
I was still wrong.

32
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,159
I'd never met Prince Chengle before,

33
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:46,800
but I knew he was deeply learned,

34
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:47,759
so deep down,

35
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:49,120
I held him in great admiration.

36
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,719
And I thought myself

37
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,719
to be well-read,

38
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,800
able to discern right from wrong.

39
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,960
But I never imagined this time

40
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,639
I'd not only misjudge a person,

41
00:03:00,759 --> 00:03:02,400
but nearly become his accomplice.

42
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,560
I'm truly utterly useless.

43
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,560
Don't be like that.

44
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:07,879
Well...

45
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,759
Even the most learned people

46
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,879
can make mistakes.

47
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:13,439
Even the smartest can be deceived.

48
00:03:13,439 --> 00:03:13,759
Uh...

49
00:03:14,159 --> 00:03:15,159
You, um...

50
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:16,199
You,

51
00:03:16,599 --> 00:03:18,000
a mere scholar, taking on

52
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:20,000
the duty of finding the heir,

53
00:03:20,439 --> 00:03:21,680
that's no easy task, right?

54
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,479
And besides,

55
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,719
you've helped many people along the way.

56
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,280
You helped Prince Mao find his first love.

57
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:30,599
You helped Prince Dai find himself.

58
00:03:31,479 --> 00:03:31,960
I mean,

59
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,840
for a weakling scholar like you,

60
00:03:34,599 --> 00:03:36,240
that's pretty impressive.

61
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:41,520
Didn't know you could comfort people.

62
00:03:42,719 --> 00:03:45,000
Prince Chengle's finally sentenced to die!

63
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,520
The murderer who killed my child

64
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,400
is finally getting the death sentence!

65
00:03:49,759 --> 00:03:51,000
When it's time for the execution,

66
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,159
you all must come and watch!

67
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:52,639
Ah!

68
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,120
He's already been sentenced to death.

69
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,840
Why make such a fuss about it?

70
00:04:00,599 --> 00:04:02,240
He deserves to die a thousand deaths!

71
00:04:03,759 --> 00:04:06,159
My Luobo had a high fever for seven days.

72
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,000
He nearly died.

73
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,400
I visited every top doctor in the city,

74
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:11,919
and none of them could help.

75
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,120
I had no choice but to beg Prince Chengle.

76
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,120
He gave me a so-called Miracle Pill,

77
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:22,600
claimed it was his life's masterwork.

78
00:04:23,399 --> 00:04:24,959
Without testing it at all,

79
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,519
he gave it to my child.

80
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,519
You didn't even test the medicine

81
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,720
before giving it to your child?

82
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,319
What else could I do?

83
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,240
But right after he took it,

84
00:04:37,399 --> 00:04:39,079
my child was gone.

85
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,600
What did you say?

86
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,240
He just disappeared all of a sudden.

87
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:44,319
So Prince Chengle didn't misdiagnose him,

88
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,920
or that he kidnapped him?

89
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:48,120
What's the difference?

90
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,240
Either way,

91
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:53,079
he's still the one who killed my child!

92
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:57,079
I'd kill him a thousand times if I could!

93
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,839
And now,

94
00:05:00,279 --> 00:05:01,519
Heaven has eyes!

95
00:05:03,959 --> 00:05:06,399
Heaven truly has eyes!

96
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,439
Brother!

97
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:12,680
Brother!

98
00:05:13,199 --> 00:05:14,000
It's me!

99
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,000
Look!

100
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,839
Sisi?

101
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:17,839
Yes!

102
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,399
Look, haven't I grown taller?

103
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:20,360
Aren't I taller?

104
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:21,360
You really have grown!

105
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:23,959
How did you grow taller?

106
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,480
The medicine the Prince gave me!

107
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:26,720
Did you forget?

108
00:05:27,439 --> 00:05:27,959
But you know,

109
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,759
for the first two months I just got fat.

110
00:05:29,839 --> 00:05:30,199
But then,

111
00:05:30,439 --> 00:05:32,000
this month I actually started growing.

112
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:33,600
That's wonderful!

113
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,800
It really worked!

114
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:35,879
You've grown taller!

115
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,399
To be honest with you,

116
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,680
because of my sister

117
00:05:43,959 --> 00:05:44,879
gaining weight from the medicine,

118
00:05:45,319 --> 00:05:46,439
the one who beat up Prince Chengle

119
00:05:46,759 --> 00:05:47,079
was me.

120
00:05:48,839 --> 00:05:49,319
See?

121
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,480
I told you Royal Brother wasn't like that.

122
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,399
Innkeeper,

123
00:05:53,839 --> 00:05:55,399
then go tell the authorities right away,

124
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,120
and get Prince Chengle's sentence reduced!

125
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,399
No, no, I can't do that.

126
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,199
Things have already blown up this badly.

127
00:06:00,199 --> 00:06:01,959
I can't go bringing trouble on myself.

128
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,839
Besides, my sister's condition,

129
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,600
anyone could have cured it.

130
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,120
Sorry, sis.

131
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:07,759
Let's head upstairs.

132
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:08,079
Alright then.

133
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:08,480
Let's go.

134
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:09,879
Hey!

135
00:06:10,399 --> 00:06:11,000
Hey!

136
00:06:11,199 --> 00:06:12,920
You're being way too selfish!

137
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:15,120
Hey...

138
00:06:15,759 --> 00:06:16,759
So does that mean

139
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,480
there are many people Royal Brother cured,

140
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,399
who are just unwilling to speak up?

141
00:06:20,519 --> 00:06:21,319
Exactly!

142
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:24,439
The Prince has practiced for years,

143
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:27,360
curing almost everyone in Chengle City.

144
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:31,000
Only in the last two years of researching

145
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,439
new treatments has he made mistakes.

146
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,279
Originally,

147
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,519
I was a gentle woman, soft as water.

148
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:41,399
The Prince made a hair-growth medicine.

149
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,279
I took it,

150
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,560
and my testosterone spiked.

151
00:06:46,759 --> 00:06:47,560
So...

152
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,319
do you hate him?

153
00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:51,839
Even though

154
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,639
I've become rugged now,

155
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,399
at least on the surface,

156
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:58,079
the Prince hasn't loved me any less.

157
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,560
He and I

158
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,680
are still as devoted as ever.

159
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,360
Besides,

160
00:07:06,879 --> 00:07:07,439
see this?

161
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,199
I'm much stronger now,

162
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,319
and a lot more energetic too.

163
00:07:13,279 --> 00:07:15,759
I actually quite like the way I am now.

164
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,600
But what good does that do?

165
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:20,879
Right now,

166
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:22,800
no one remembers Royal Brother's kindness.

167
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,199
Maybe so.

168
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Either way, he's a dead man walking.

169
00:07:28,399 --> 00:07:29,079
No.

170
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,360
He can't die.

171
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,560
Since he committed no crime,

172
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:35,120
we have to save him.

173
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,600
But how are you going to save him?

174
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:42,759
Hey, where are you going?

175
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,600
Hey!

176
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:45,600
Just let him go on his own.

177
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:53,600
Halt!

178
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:54,800
Oh.

179
00:07:55,439 --> 00:07:57,079
I'd like to see Prince Chengle.

180
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,360
A death-row prisoner?

181
00:07:58,839 --> 00:08:00,000
You can't just see him on a whim.

182
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:01,959
Brother, brother,

183
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:02,879
cut us some slack.

184
00:08:02,879 --> 00:08:03,439
Be flexible, please.

185
00:08:03,439 --> 00:08:03,680
Huh?

186
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,040
Just bend the rules a bit.

187
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:05,600
Huh?

188
00:08:09,519 --> 00:08:11,680
You're asking to see a death-row inmate!

189
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,839
Hey,

190
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,120
times are tough for everyone.

191
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:15,839
Here.

192
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,120
Do us this favor.

193
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,680
You're quite the loyal friend,

194
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,480
actually willing, for a friend's sake,

195
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,040
to spend money like that.

196
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,120
What's gotten into you?

197
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,000
You think I wanted to?

198
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:38,320
I...

199
00:08:47,759 --> 00:08:48,200
Prince

200
00:08:48,919 --> 00:08:50,240
You're about to be executed

201
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:52,159
yet you're still so calm.

202
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:54,879
Panicking won't solve anything.

203
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,159
I knew this day would come.

204
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,000
Even now, you still pretend

205
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,159
to be all-knowing?

206
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:00,960
Hey.

207
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,159
Qi Zhi.

208
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:05,159
I won't hide it from you.

209
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:06,519
I do

210
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,320
occasionally engage in

211
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,919
some shady dealings,

212
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,080
doing things that deceive the world.

213
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,639
But that's just how I survive.

214
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:17,120
I study medicine

215
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,320
not to save the world,

216
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:23,080
nor to cure any one person.

217
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,519
I just want medicine to progress,

218
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,519
to make broader,

219
00:09:27,679 --> 00:09:28,720
deeper progress.

220
00:09:29,679 --> 00:09:30,840
For that, I made mistakes.

221
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,360
Daliang Kingdom's law must punish me,

222
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,519
and I have nothing to say about it.

223
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:39,759
I asked around the city.

224
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,720
Many people said

225
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,039
your pills cured them.

226
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:46,360
Though they're grateful,

227
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,720
none dare to speak up for you.

228
00:09:50,039 --> 00:09:50,720
Heh heh.

229
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,519
Whether they're grateful or not,

230
00:09:52,519 --> 00:09:53,960
I don't care one bit.

231
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,919
Qi Zhi,

232
00:10:12,159 --> 00:10:13,159
you're my only true friend.

233
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,120
I've

234
00:10:15,519 --> 00:10:17,360
written every theory I've learned

235
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,120
in my lifetime into this book.

236
00:10:21,279 --> 00:10:22,279
Keep it safe.

237
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:23,960
With it,

238
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,480
Daliang Kingdom's medicine

239
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,720
will advance by at least 50 years.

240
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,519
And that pill,

241
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,720
pass it down through the ages.

242
00:10:31,879 --> 00:10:32,480
Will you?

243
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:57,759
Retry Prince Chengle! Retry Prince Chengle!

244
00:10:57,759 --> 00:10:58,720
Retry him! Retry him!

245
00:10:58,879 --> 00:10:59,639
Stop your shouting!

246
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:01,200
Retry Prince Chengle! Retry Prince Chengle!

247
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:02,159
What do you all want?

248
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:05,159
Retry him! Retry him!

249
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:09,240
Retry Prince Chengle! Retry Prince Chengle!

250
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,840
Retry him! Retry him!

251
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,639
My Lord.

252
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:13,759
My Lord.

253
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,519
A crowd has gathered outside

254
00:11:15,559 --> 00:11:16,960
demanding a retrial for Prince Chengle.

255
00:11:17,879 --> 00:11:18,679
Nonsense!

256
00:11:19,559 --> 00:11:21,639
You can't just retry a case on demand!

257
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:24,080
These are people Prince Chengle cured.

258
00:11:24,279 --> 00:11:25,679
They came today to plead his case.

259
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,639
They said

260
00:11:26,639 --> 00:11:27,960
they had unspeakable illnesses

261
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,720
that only Prince Chengle could cure.

262
00:11:30,159 --> 00:11:30,960
But

263
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:32,960
they seem to be hiding their conditions,

264
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:35,320
and no one's willing to testify for him.

265
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:39,639
There's such a thing?

266
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:49,360
Prince Chengle.

267
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:49,879
Hmm.

268
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,679
Let's go.

269
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,159
Oh.

270
00:11:56,279 --> 00:11:58,080
When will this drug wear off?

271
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,120
Thank you all for your hard work.

272
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:01,519
Here.

273
00:12:01,519 --> 00:12:02,440
Have some water.

274
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:04,440
Drink some hot water.

275
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,240
Warm yourselves up.

276
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:09,879
Even though the Crown Prince is here,

277
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:11,320
and you're a palace envoy,

278
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,360
the law treats everyone equally.

279
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:14,720
You

280
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,519
cannot protect him.

281
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:17,519
My Lord,

282
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,879
I only wish to help everyone prove

283
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,360
that though Prince Chengle is guilty,

284
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:22,720
his crime doesn't warrant death.

285
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,600
He sold counterfeit medicine,

286
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,519
harmed the people,

287
00:12:26,519 --> 00:12:27,679
and caused infants to vanish.

288
00:12:28,519 --> 00:12:30,360
Are these not the facts?

289
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,240
Madam Wei,

290
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,799
whatever grievance you have,

291
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:36,039
feel free to speak.

292
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:39,960
It was him.

293
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:41,960
He caused my child's death.

294
00:12:43,639 --> 00:12:44,720
My child

295
00:12:44,919 --> 00:12:47,080
was sent to Liu Yan's home for treatment,

296
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,519
but never returned.

297
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:52,360
No sign of him, alive or dead.

298
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,480
I went to find Liu Yan,

299
00:12:55,039 --> 00:12:56,519
but he kept making excuses,

300
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,879
refusing to tell me where my child was.

301
00:13:00,519 --> 00:13:01,320
My Lord,

302
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:04,320
I beg you to grant me justice!

303
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:05,600
My Lord.

304
00:13:08,039 --> 00:13:08,840
Prince Chengle,

305
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,639
Hmm?

306
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:11,360
What do you have to say in your defense?

307
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:13,759
I have nothing to say.

308
00:13:15,159 --> 00:13:15,960
My Lord,

309
00:13:16,159 --> 00:13:16,879
I have something to say.

310
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,000
I have a piece of evidence

311
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,840
that can prove Prince Chengle's innocence.

312
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:20,639
Hey!

313
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:21,720
What are you doing?

314
00:13:22,279 --> 00:13:23,559
This is my only Miracle Pill left.

315
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,320
Let it be passed down, all right?

316
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:27,120
Would anyone believe you anyway?

317
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:30,960
Since

318
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,279
Prince Chengle has admitted his crimes,

319
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:34,799
further trial

320
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,519
is no longer necessary.

321
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:37,919
Guards!

322
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,039
Take him away.

323
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,879
Prince Chengle isn't that kind of man.

324
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:41,559
That's right.

325
00:13:41,679 --> 00:13:42,840
The growth medicine he gave me back then

326
00:13:42,919 --> 00:13:43,840
really did work.

327
00:13:44,159 --> 00:13:45,039
Yes, yes.

328
00:13:45,159 --> 00:13:46,480
Even though I overate,

329
00:13:46,519 --> 00:13:48,080
when he gave me the prescription,

330
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,720
he kept urging me to lose weight.

331
00:13:50,159 --> 00:13:51,360
When I was once on the verge of death,

332
00:13:51,639 --> 00:13:52,919
he gave me medicine to cure my anorexia.

333
00:13:52,919 --> 00:13:54,320
That gave me the strength to keep living.

334
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:00,960
I'm sorry, Prince.

335
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,639
I can't just watch you die.

336
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,360
My Lord.

337
00:14:06,799 --> 00:14:07,960
This pill in my hand

338
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,240
is the very Longevity Pill

339
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,399
Prince Chengle gave the infant.

340
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,759
Words alone prove nothing.

341
00:14:11,919 --> 00:14:13,279
As for what it does,

342
00:14:13,679 --> 00:14:14,720
once I take it,

343
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,759
we'll see for ourselves.

344
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:18,159
Hey!

345
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:19,120
Hey!

346
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:19,679
Prince!

347
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:20,639
Prince!

348
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,360
Prince!

349
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,639
Hey, how did he turn small?

350
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,120
Prince! Prince!

351
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:30,320
Prince Chengle.

352
00:14:33,279 --> 00:14:34,279
So that's how it is.

353
00:14:35,679 --> 00:14:37,279
Prince Chengle's Longevity Pill

354
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,840
doesn't actually extend one's life.

355
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:42,159
Instead, it makes people younger.

356
00:14:44,919 --> 00:14:47,120
When you gave him your child,

357
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:49,720
he knew the child was beyond saving.

358
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,639
So he took a desperate gamble

359
00:14:51,879 --> 00:14:53,440
and gave the child the Longevity Pill.

360
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:55,840
But because the infant was so young,

361
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:57,120
after taking the pill,

362
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,159
he vanished completely.

363
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:02,080
But he couldn't explain it,

364
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,960
because unless one witnessed it firsthand,

365
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,399
no one would believe

366
00:15:05,399 --> 00:15:06,879
that such an absurd thing could exist.

367
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,240
This...

368
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,039
In our Daliang Kingdom,

369
00:15:11,039 --> 00:15:12,320
nothing like this has ever happened.

370
00:15:15,279 --> 00:15:16,360
How am I supposed to rule on this?

371
00:15:17,639 --> 00:15:18,440
I...

372
00:15:20,039 --> 00:15:21,360
I really don't know what to do.

373
00:15:23,759 --> 00:15:24,519
My Lord,

374
00:15:25,159 --> 00:15:27,279
please let me raise this infant.

375
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:32,720
The Prince became this way for my son.

376
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,759
I want to raise him well,

377
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,960
so he can be our Prince again someday.

378
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:39,879
May I?

379
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:40,559
Well...

380
00:15:41,639 --> 00:15:42,960
I suppose that's the only option.

381
00:15:43,559 --> 00:15:44,720
Thank you, My Lord.

382
00:15:55,519 --> 00:15:56,519
Prince, don't cry.

383
00:15:56,519 --> 00:15:57,360
We're leaving now.

384
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:57,960
Be a good boy.

385
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,960
Take good care of yourself.

386
00:16:03,039 --> 00:16:03,320
Oh dear.

387
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:04,519
Oh dear.

388
00:16:04,919 --> 00:16:06,320
I won't say goodbye.

389
00:16:06,559 --> 00:16:06,840
It's...

390
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,279
it's too embarrassing.

391
00:16:10,039 --> 00:16:10,919
Take care, everyone.

392
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:19,679
What happened to my Royal Brother

393
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,519
is truly heartbreaking.

394
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:24,519
Luckily, I'm not under that much pressure.

395
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:26,559
I just want to draw my comics.

396
00:16:26,759 --> 00:16:28,159
Of course you have no pressure.

397
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,679
You pushed all the pressure onto this guy.

398
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:32,360
How could you possibly have any?

399
00:16:35,519 --> 00:16:35,799
Oh.

400
00:16:35,919 --> 00:16:36,360
That reminds me.

401
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,720
My mission is complete.

402
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:38,200
Now I

403
00:16:38,639 --> 00:16:39,639
must take the Truth Pill back.

404
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,279
You two,

405
00:16:41,279 --> 00:16:41,960
take good care.

406
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,159
Farewell.

407
00:16:48,919 --> 00:16:50,720
It seems the people of this city

408
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,399
still hold Prince Chengle dear.

409
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:54,519
No.

410
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,519
Not a single person

411
00:16:58,519 --> 00:17:00,320
would speak up for Prince Chengle.

412
00:17:00,679 --> 00:17:01,639
Then how come...

413
00:17:02,679 --> 00:17:03,600
The human heart...

414
00:17:04,039 --> 00:17:05,759
truly does need a pill to heal it.

415
00:17:23,119 --> 00:17:23,720
Who would have thought

416
00:17:24,319 --> 00:17:25,319
So that's how it is.

417
00:17:27,519 --> 00:17:29,960
Although Prince Chengle keeps insisting

418
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,759
that he doesn't care if they live or die,

419
00:17:32,759 --> 00:17:35,279
when he saw the infant in critical danger,

420
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,119
he still stepped in to save it,

421
00:17:37,119 --> 00:17:38,119
taking the risk.

422
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:41,960
The Prince poured half his life's effort

423
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,519
into researching those baffling illnesses,

424
00:17:44,039 --> 00:17:45,960
treating those rare diseases

425
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,920
that ordinary doctors refuse to take on.

426
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,079
Hopefully, one day,

427
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:52,519
the world will understand his intentions.

428
00:18:01,279 --> 00:18:02,319
Why is it you again?

429
00:18:02,759 --> 00:18:04,160
Can you stop following us?

430
00:18:04,519 --> 00:18:04,799
Hey!

431
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:06,839
I won't, I won't, I won't!

432
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:07,960
Hmph!

433
00:18:13,519 --> 00:18:15,119
The drug has finally worn off.

434
00:18:16,759 --> 00:18:17,000
Hmm.

435
00:18:20,319 --> 00:18:21,119
Bring in the prisoner.

436
00:18:29,839 --> 00:18:30,640
Ugh.

437
00:18:43,599 --> 00:18:43,880
Speak!

438
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,640
Who exactly was it

439
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,119
that took the poison from you?

440
00:18:48,559 --> 00:18:49,960
It was Eunuch Gao.

441
00:18:50,759 --> 00:18:51,559
Eunuch Gao?

442
00:18:55,839 --> 00:18:57,559
Didn't you say General Li last time?

443
00:19:00,359 --> 00:19:03,519
He captured my entire family of thirteen.

444
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:06,759
I had no choice but to say that.

445
00:19:07,759 --> 00:19:08,720
Is this the truth?

446
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:13,079
Not a single word is false.

447
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:19,319
Take him away.

448
00:19:19,319 --> 00:19:19,960
Guard him closely.

449
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:20,960
Yes, My Lord.

450
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,119
Master,

451
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:29,960
what should we do now?

452
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:33,920
Your Highness,

453
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,039
we can turn their scheme against them.
